headline: Affirm Stock Slips After Earnings. Analysts Say That’s Unwarranted.
summary: The reaction is unwarranted, some analysts said.  Revenue of $1.12 billion beat analysts’ calls for $1.06 billion, according to FactSet.  Gross merchandise volume rose 36% to $13.8 billion, a “record” for the company,  Affirm  said, and higher than the $13.3 billion Wall Street had forecast.
